                           <locus target="#2va">Fols. 2va-3</locus>ra: Excerpt from an unidentified apocalypse (?).  <q xml:lang="gez">Fols. 2v-3r: በዳንኤል፡ በ፩፡&lt;…&gt;ለእመ፡ ኮነ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ በሰኑይ፡ ክዕወተ፡ ደም፡ ይበዝኅ፡ ብእሲት፡ ደም፡ ይውኅዝ፡ ከመ፡ ማይ፡ ነድ፡ ይከውን፡ መኳንንት፡ ዓበይት፡ ይመውቱ፡…</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The name of the scribe was erased; the second part of the name is still partially legible and can probably be read as Maryam.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#197rb">Fols. 197rb</locus>-va: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fols. 197rb-va: ዝንቱ፡ መጽሕፈ፡ ግንዘት፡ ዘወሀባ፡ ለማርያም፡ ገበዘይት፡ ዘወሀብዋ፡ አቤቶ፡ ሀጎስ፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ፡ መርሃ፡ መንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ኢትርስዑነ፡ በጸሎትክሙ፡ ፩፩ አቡነ፡ ዘበሰማያት። ዘምድረ፡ ዓድ፡ ኢለማ፡ ዘወሀብዋ፡ ደጅ፡ አዝማች፡ ዘመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ለዛቲ፡ ምድር፡ ሥሉስ፡ ወዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘሄደ፡ ወዛተ፡ ዓገላ፡ ዘሰረቃ፡ ወዘፈቃ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ይኩን፡ በቃለ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጰውሎስ፡ ወ፫ቱ፡ ፻፡ ፲ወ፪፡ ሐዋርያት።  </q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note has been written, in the main hand, in red ink. The note is not quite clear; it states that the Ms. was donated by ʾabeto Hagos to the church Maryam Gäbäzäyti. ʾAbeto Hagos (d. 1831, baptismal name Dǝgǝmawi Zä-Mänfäs Qǝddus) was a son of däğğazmač Säbagadis (baptismal name Zä-Mänfäs Qǝddus, s. EAE IV, 431; cf. Ms. FBM-002). The note mentions also a land donation to ʿAdd ʾIlama.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title of the Ms. is written: fol. 198v.&#xD;
- Crude drawing of a human with a spear, Legend: Gäbrä Giyorgis: fol. 198v.&#xD;
- Crude drawing of a cross: fol. 197v.&#xD;
- Part of the line is taken up: fols. 21r, 86v.&#xD;
- Part of the line is taken down: fol. 10v.&#xD;
- Omitted letters, words and passages are inserted interlineally or written in the margin on many fols.: e.g., fols. 4v, 5r, 11r, 29r, 37r, 56r, 73v, 109v.&#xD;
- Corrections written over erasures on several fols.: e.g., fols. 36r, 42v, 72v, 87r, 99r, 106r, 134r.&#xD;
- Erasures: fols. 95v, 145r, 195v.&#xD;
- The scribe used compressed script: e.g., fols. 38va-40ra, 64va-65vb, 71rb-72ra.&#xD;
- Pen trials, scribbles and doodles: fols. 86r, 116r, 178v, 197v, 198r.</item>
